Kuwait National Petroleum Co. (9937)  plans
to build a third refinery in  Asia  in addition to projects in
China and  Vietnam , according to a company official.  The three refineries would have a total capacity of 600,000
barrels a day, Bakhit al-Rashidi, KPCâ€™s deputy managing
director, said in an interview in  Tokyo  today. No decision has
been made on where the third refinery will be located, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
